servings: 2
---

In a small #pot, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

== Spicy Pickles ==

In a medium #bowl, combine cucumber, scallion greens, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, and as much @sriracha{1/4-1/2%tsp} as you like (1⁄2 tsp sugar and 1⁄2 tsp salt for 4 servings).

Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

== Beef Bulgogi ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz} and scallion whites; season with @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. (Carefully drain any excess grease from pan.)

Stir @bulgogi sauce{4%oz} and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} into pan with beef mixture until evenly coated.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork. Divide lettuce leaves between plates. Fill with rice, beef bulgogi, and as many spicy pickles (draining first) as you like. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.